overview: Woodstock '99 was the second large-scale music festival (after Woodstock '94) that attempted to emulate the original Woodstock festival of 1969. Day 2 (July 24, 1999) features performances by Everclear, Dave Mathews Band, Los Lobos, Alanis Morissette, Limp Bizkit, Mickey Hart & Planet Drum, Ice Cube, Rage Against the Machine, The Chemical Brothers, and Metallica.
title: Woodstock '99: Day 2
